ob006","id":5972388,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5NzIzODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5972388?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006","html_url":"https://github.com/rob006","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2017-11-11T16:21:40Z","updated_at":"2017-11-11T16:21:40Z","body":"> this behavior is inconsistent with the way validators are working in model classes\r\n\r\nBecause model validation simply works differently and most of the settings will not work on `validate()` call. \r\nAnd `skipOnEmpty` does not mean \"treat empty results as valid\" but \"do not run validation on attribute if it is empty\".\r\n\r\nChanging this will break BC.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/comments/343676065/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"rob006","id":5972388,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5NzIzODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5972388?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006","html_url":"https://github.com/rob006","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/comments/343680048","html_url":"https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/issues/15145#issuecomment-343680048","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/15145","id":343680048,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MzY4MDA0OA==","user":{"login":"hesna","id":2319368,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTkzNjg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2319368?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna","html_url":"https://github.com/hesna","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2017-11-11T17:23:59Z","updated_at":"2017-11-11T17:27:57Z","body":"> Because model validation simply works differently and most of the settings will not work on validate() call.\r\n\r\nit's better to support as much same features for both model based and ad hoc validation as possible, as they both share the same class. otherwise it's better to introduce new validator classes specific for ad hoc usages, instead of creating the same object and assuming it would just work differently based on where you use it.\r\nas it's stated on official docs, some validators do not support ad hoc usage at all, but for a situation like the example I gave, it just makes sense to set `skipOnEmpty` property and expect it to work!\r\n\r\n> And skipOnEmpty does not mean \"treat empty results as valid\" but \"do not run validation on attribute if it is empty\".\r\n\r\nyou're right, but eventually it causes validator to ignore input thus not adding any errors to $errors array, causing a validate call return true.\r\n\r\n> Changing this will break BC.\r\n\r\npeople should use `yii\\validators\\RequiredValidator` class if they need their input fields to be filled. not sure if people relying on unexpected behaviors should keep us from making things better.","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/comments/343680048/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"hesna","id":2319368,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTkzNjg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2319368?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna","html_url":"https://github.com/hesna","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/comments/343680621","html_url":"https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/issues/15145#issuecomment-343680621","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/15145","id":343680621,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MzY4MDYyMQ==","user":{"login":"rob006","id":5972388,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5NzIzODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5972388?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006","html_url":"https://github.com/rob006","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2017-11-11T17:32:14Z","updated_at":"2017-11-11T17:32:14Z","body":"> people should use yii\\validators\\RequiredValidator class if they need their input fields to be filled. not sure if people relying on unexpected behaviors should keep us from making things better.\r\n\r\nDoes empty string is a valid email address? No. If `EmailValidator::validate()` will start returning `true` for invalid values, this will be not only confusing, this is simple a bug. I will never call this \"making things better\".","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/comments/343680621/reactions","total_count":5,"+1":5,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"rob006","id":5972388,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5NzIzODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5972388?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006","html_url":"https://github.com/rob006","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rob006/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/comments/343688031","html_url":"https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/issues/15145#issuecomment-343688031","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yiisoft/yii2/issues/15145","id":343688031,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0MzY4ODAzMQ==","user":{"login":"hesna","id":2319368,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIzMTkzNjg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2319368?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna","html_url":"https://github.com/hesna","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hesna/subscriptions","organizations_